Events Calendar 3.12.5. This is a fresh release straight off the heels of yesterday&#8217;s minor update. In fact, if you updated yesterday, then we encourage you to do the same today because this includes a fix for an issue that came up in the forums this&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-5/">Release: The Events Calendar 3.12.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1556:"<p>Hey, we&#8217;re here to let you know about The Events Calendar 3.12.5. This is a fresh release straight off the heels of yesterday&#8217;s minor update. In fact, if you updated yesterday, then we encourage you to do the same today because this includes a fix for an issue that came up in the forums this morning:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Restore styling and full mobile functionality to month view</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In other words, there was an issue where the current day was not highlighting in Month View. This was the result of a compiling issue we hit when creating the last update, but now we&#8217;re in the clear. Thanks a ton to Rich Cottee for initially <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/topic/update-breaks-todays-date-highlighting-on-tribe-events-template/">reporting this</a>!</p>\n<p>As always, please use caution when updating from version 3.11 or lower. We suggest reading through the <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/category/products/release-notes/">release notes</a> before updating from earlier versions and testing in a development environment with backups as you would any other WordPress update.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your support! We appreciate everyone in the community here for helping make The Events Calendar awesome.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-5/">Release: The Events Calendar 3.12.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-5/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Release: Community Tickets 3.12";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-tickets-3-12/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-tickets-3-12/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 04 Nov 2015 22:11:06 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Release Notes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1021787";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:573:"<p>Hello, howdy and good day to everyone. I&#8217;m stoked to be writing this post because it marks the debut of our new premium Community Tickets plugin! This has been in the works for some time now and is the result of one of our most-requested features. We&#8217;ve long heard from many folks to provide a solution that&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-tickets-3-12/">Release: Community Tickets 3.12</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2156:"<p>Hello, howdy and good day to everyone. I&#8217;m stoked to be writing this post because it marks <strong>the debut of our new premium Community Tickets plugin!</strong></p>\n<p>This has been in the works for some time now and is the result of <a href="http://tribe.uservoice.com/forums/195723-feature-ideas/suggestions/4409106-allow-community-events-users-to-add-tickets-via-fr">one of our most-requested features</a>. We&#8217;ve long heard from many folks to provide a solution that combines the power of front-end event submissions of <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/">Community Events</a> with the ticket-selling wonders of <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-wootickets/">WooCommerce Tickets</a>.</p>\n<p>Well, that&#8217;s now possible and available today with the release of <strong>Community Tickets 3.12</strong>. This new plugin — when used with Community Events and WooCommerce Tickets — allows your website visitors to create and sell tickets for the events they submit to the site&#8217;s calendar.</p>\n<p>This is the initial release of the plugin, so there are no release notes to share other than that everything is brand-spanking new! It&#8217;s pretty rad and we hope you love it as much as we&#8217;ve enjoyed working on it.</p>\n<p>If you do plan on purchasing and using Community Tickets, please do grab or update to the latest versions of The Events Calendar, Community Events and WooCommerce Tickets as well to ensure everything works nicely together. And, if something doesn&#8217;t seem to be working well or you have some questions for us, <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/forum/events/community-tickets/">we have a new forum available</a> specifically for Community Tickets for you. Open a new thread and our support team would be happy to help.</p>\n<p>Cheers and happy calendaring!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-tickets-3-12/">Release: Community Tickets 3.12</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-tickets-3-12/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"Release: WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-woocommerce-tickets-3-12-1/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-woocommerce-tickets-3-12-1/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 04 Nov 2015 22:10:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Release Notes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1021785";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:633:"<p>Hey everyone and happy Wednesday! We have released a minor update to our premium WooCommerce Tickets add-on for The Events Calendar and wanted to let you know about it. WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1 adds support for the brand-new premium Community Tickets plugin that also released today. In fact, you will notice no functional difference in WooCommerce Tickets if you are&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-woocommerce-tickets-3-12-1/">Release: WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2465:"<p>Hey everyone and happy Wednesday! We have released a minor update to our premium <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-wootickets/">WooCommerce Tickets</a> add-on for The Events Calendar and wanted to let you know about it.</p>\n<p><strong>WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1</strong> adds support for the brand-new premium <a href="http://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a> plugin that also released today. In fact, you will notice no functional difference in WooCommerce Tickets if you are upgrading from 3.12.</p>\n<p>A <a href="http://tribe.uservoice.com/forums/195723-feature-ideas/suggestions/4409106-allow-community-events-users-to-add-tickets-via-fr">popular feature request</a> has been to provide a way to connect our <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/">Community Events</a> and <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-wootickets/">WooCommerce Tickets</a> plugins together. In other words, a way to allow people to not inly submit events to The Events Calendar from the front-end of the site, but a way to create and sell tickets for those events as well. That&#8217;s now a possibility when updating to WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1 and adding both <a href="http://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a> and <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-wootickets/">WooCommerce Tickets</a> to the mix. The three, when used together, will create that event submission and ticket selling powerhouse that many have been looking for!</p>\n<p>We expect smooth sailing and no breakages if you&#8217;re upgrading from WooCommerce Tickets 3.12 or greater. However, if you&#8217;re upgrading from 3.11 or earlier, please do read through <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/category/products/release-notes/">the release notes</a> for the versions that have come out since and make sure to test the updates in a development environment before using on a live site—especially if you have made any customizations to the plugin. And, as always, back up your files and database as you would with any other WordPress update.</p>\n<p>Cheers and happy calendaring!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-woocommerce-tickets-3-12-1/">Release: WooCommerce Tickets 3.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-woocommerce-tickets-3-12-1/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"Release: Community Events 3.12.1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-events-3-12-1/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-events-3-12-1/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 04 Nov 2015 22:10:52 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Release Notes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1021780";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:597:"<p>Hey everyone and happy Wednesday! We have released a minor update to our premium Community Events add-on for The Events Calendar and wanted to let you know about it. So, what&#8217;s new in Community Events 3.12.1? Well, nothing really. In fact, you will notice no functional difference if you are upgrading from 3.12. What this update does,&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-events-3-12-1/">Release: Community Events 3.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2225:"<p>Hey everyone and happy Wednesday! We have released a minor update to our premium <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-community-events/">Community Events</a> add-on for The Events Calendar and wanted to let you know about it.</p>\n<p>So, what&#8217;s new in <strong>Community Events 3.12.1</strong>? Well, nothing really. In fact, you will notice no functional difference if you are upgrading from 3.12. What this update does, however, is set the stage for the brand new <a href="http://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a>, which just so happens to release today.</p>\n<p>We have received <a href="http://tribe.uservoice.com/forums/195723-feature-ideas/suggestions/4409106-allow-community-events-users-to-add-tickets-via-fr">a ton of folks asking for a feature</a> that allows people who submit events through Community Events to create and sell tickets for those events as well. That is now possible when updating to Community Events 3.12.1 and adding both <a href="http://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a> and <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-wootickets/">WooCommerce Tickets</a>. The combination of these three plugins together creates a trifecta of awesomeness that opens your site up to a new level of interaction and doing business.</p>\n<p>We expect smooth sailing and no breakages if you&#8217;re upgrading from Community Events 3.12 or greater. However, if you&#8217;re upgrading from 3.11 or earlier, please do read through <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/category/products/release-notes/">the release notes</a> for the versions that have come out since and make sure to test the updates in a development environment before using on a live site—especially if you have made any customizations to the calendar. And, as always, back up your files and database as you would with any other WordPress update.</p>\n<p>Cheers and happy calendaring!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-events-3-12-1/">Release: Community Events 3.12.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-community-events-3-12-1/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"Release: The Events Calendar 3.12.4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-4/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-4/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 04 Nov 2015 22:10:40 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Release Notes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1021774";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:561:"<p>Happy Wednesday, ladies and gents! We have a fresh release of The Events Calendar ready for you and are excited for you to check it out. The Events Calendar 3.12.4 is a minor release that sets the stage for our big 4.0 release around the corner. It also adds integration and support for the brand new&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-4/">Release: The Events Calendar 3.12.4</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1594:"<p>Happy Wednesday, ladies and gents! We have a fresh release of The Events Calendar ready for you and are excited for you to check it out.</p>\n<p><strong>The Events Calendar 3.12.4</strong> is a minor release that sets the stage for our big 4.0 release around the corner. It also adds integration and support for the brand new <a href="http://theeventscalendar.com/product/community-tickets/">Community Tickets</a>, which just so happens to release today as well.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s what&#8217;s new:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Added support for the new Events Community Tickets plugin</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Wrapping functions in conditionals to avoid fatals in our upcoming 4.0 release</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We expect smooth sailing and no breakages if you&#8217;re upgrading from The Events Calendar 3.12 or greater. However, if you&#8217;re upgrading from 3.11 or earlier, please do read through <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/category/products/release-notes/">the release notes</a> for the versions that have come out since and make sure to test the updates in a development environment before using on a live site—especially if you have made any customizations to the calendar. And, as always, back up your files and database as you would with any other WordPress update.</p>\n<p>Cheers and happy calendaring!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-4/">Release: The Events Calendar 3.12.4</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-the-events-calendar-3-12-4/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"Release: Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-pro-3-12-5/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-pro-3-12-5/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 28 Oct 2015 20:32:01 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Release Notes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1019389";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:597:"<p>Happy Wednesday, folks! We&#8217;ve squeezed in a quick, but important maintenance release to Events Calendar PRO and wanted to let you know it&#8217;s available at this very moment. Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5 addresses a small, but significant issue that was called out to us on Twitter and here on the forums regarding Photo View. This&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-pro-3-12-5/">Release: Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Geoff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2231:"<p>Happy Wednesday, folks! We&#8217;ve squeezed in a quick, but important maintenance release to Events Calendar PRO and wanted to let you know it&#8217;s available at this very moment.</p>\n<p><strong>Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5</strong> addresses a small, but significant issue that was called out to us on Twitter and here on the forums regarding Photo View. This release patches javascript errors that were popping up when geolocation was enabled in the map settings, but the event did not have any geolocation data available.</p>\n<p>We also snuck in a little feature that re-introduces the ability to name custom recurrences. In fact, here is what we documented in the changelog:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix &#8211; </strong>Resolve JS errors on various views where geolocation data is anticipated but unavailable (thanks to @jesse_fo and everyone else who reported this)</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Bring back the Recurrence Rule description override field</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you&#8217;re already using Events Calendar PRO 3.12 or greater, then it&#8217;s a good idea to update. If you haven&#8217;t made the jump to 3.12, then please do <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-version-3-12-of-the-events-calendar-pro-and-all-add-ons/">check out the notes for that release</a> and be sure to test before updating because there were a number of significant updates between 3.11 and 3.12 you should be aware of if you&#8217;ve made any customizations.</p>\n<p>If you have auto-updates enabled on your site, you should see Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5 pop up in your WordPress Updates list very soon. However, you can also grab a copy by logging into the site here and heading to <strong>My Account → Downloads</strong>.</p>\n<p>As always, happy updating and thanks for your support! Please feel free to hit us up <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/">here in the forums</a> if you have any issues while updating and we&#8217;d be happy to help.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-pro-3-12-5/">Release: Events Calendar PRO 3.12.5</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10