(156, 45, 'hazard', 'a:5:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:"title";s:52:"Toilet height too low – difficult to sit and stand";s:14:"hazard_content";s:116:"Comfort height toilet or raised toilet seat.\r\nGrab bars installed on both sides of the toilet, or nearby the toilet.";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:"title";s:20:"Reaching for objects";s:14:"hazard_content";s:216:"Accessible storage for frequently used items.\r\nAdditional storage to reduce clutter.\r\nLocate clothes hooks above eye level (in current house).\r\nSelect easy-to-grasp D- or U-shaped pulls for cabinet doors and drawers.";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:"title";s:35:"Slippery surfaces in shower or bath";s:14:"hazard_content";s:381:"Anti-skid strips on tub/shower floor.\r\nBath mats with rubberized backing.\r\nChoose flooring materials that are textured, slip-resistant/anti-slip tiles, even-surfaced, low-glare, durable and easy to maintain. \r\nSelect a tub or shower with a nonslip surface.\r\nLarge shower designed as a walk-in, little or no threshold or lip to step over, roll-in, curbless or European-style shower.";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:"title";s:31:"Inadequate support in bath area";s:14:"hazard_content";s:351:"Hand-held shower hose. \r\nShower bench/seat installed to the shower, either built-in or fold-down, with integrated grab bars.\r\nInstall L-shaped or horizontal grab bars, capable of supporting a person weighing 250lbs, in tub and shower areas.\r\nHorizontal grab bar installed on the rear wall of the tub.\r\nVertical grab bars installed on the shower walls.";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:"title";s:19:"Inadequate lighting";s:14:"hazard_content";s:95:"Include nightlights.\r\nLight located near or above the shower and/or bathtub (in current house).";}}'),
